        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:42PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rogersville, or 14 miles northwest of Athens, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Athens, Rogersville, Ardmore, Tanner, Elkmont, Anderson,
Lester, Good Springs, and Belle Mina.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
